                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4419: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-05T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 5, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 5—9:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>246. Li Yuan-hung replies to Kao En-hung<note n="48" xml:id="d470fn48">Chinese
                        Minister of Communications.</note> Cabinet that he will resume Presidency if
                    Generals Wu Pei-fu and Tsao Kun will agree to troops’ disbandment and abolition
                    everywhere post of Military Governor. Same delegate Kao En-hung proceeding to
                    Paotingfu this morning to present these conditions which it is assumed will be
                    accepted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
